originalText.text: Call center employee (Jasmine) incapable of respectful conversation. Wife needs to bring a baby to her appointment and they supposedly have a policy with no under 12's. Asked once, the employee asks a supervisor where the policy is. She asked if we called before and I said yes and tried to explain why. Which caused her to melt down "I know why you called!"... why so rude? She continued to melt down and profess she was ignorant of anything to help me and needed the supervisor to respond but that she "knows what you're getting at" and doesn't need it explained. Gross service. This office deserves the low rating. I can see how Robert Hadden molested 79 patients with no one caring

originalText.text: Recommended by a friend, I called to make an emergency appointment for something and was told it should be about a week. At that point, it was fine and I could wait. I was told a nurse would reach out, and nobody did so I called a week later and was told the same thing. I said it could be anybody, nothing specific, I just really needed to see somebody. It’s now been five weeks since I first called and I’ve called every week in an attempt to get an appointment so I wouldn’t have the same recurring problem and I’ve still never even been contacted to schedule an appointment. Each time I speak to someone they seem shocked I haven’t still been contacted and say they’ll put another note in that this is an emergency. Obviously they do not care much because it’s been over a month… definitely will not be coming here, and plan to look elsewhere.
